reviewText: I picked this up for $79.99 from Amazon. This was another series I got into halfway through, and caught up watching syndication episodes on A&E. Every season is good except for the last. Too many story lines left hanging, and only 19 episodes were released due to the series cancellation. Learned much CSI work watching this show, and the technical aspects of this show were outstanding to watch. Will be screening this again and again for the quality that was evident in producing this show.
summary: The Complete Series at an affordable price.

reviewText: I bought this set for $59 during an Amazon Christmas sale. There are 65 disks in this complete series collection, so that translates to less than $1 per disk. I've watched a few episodes on TV, but now I can watch these at my leisure without commercials. This is the reason I have dropped my cable: I can buy TV series on DVD at really reasonable prices. For the $110 per month I used to pay for my cable bill, I can buy DVD series and own them (and sell or trade after I have finished, if I don't want to  keep the series). CSI Miami is exciting and complete eye-candy, not just the handsome actors, but also the beautiful lighting and vibrant colors in the way that this series was filmed. During these dark and cold winter months, it's great to be transported to the sun and decadence of Miami.
